dashboardItems.text: This sections provides actuals at both registration and distribution phases. These are derived using the summary reporting form.
This section enables monitoring of daily performance. The data source is the summary form (except where variances are shown, which use both the summary form and the digital register).

This section highlights overall campaign results. Columns with the text "TRK" are derived using the digital register. All others are derived using data reported through the summary form.

🔴 0 to <85 (Red)
🟡 85 to <95 (Yellow)
🟢 95+ (Green)

reportTables.description:
Objective: To ensure registered households are reached at distribution

Calculation:
- Num: # registered households issued ITNs
- Den: # registered households

Action: If under 100%, identify areas of low reach and adapt strategy (e.g. SBC, follow-up) to reach households.
reportTables.name: ITN MC - Proportion of registered households receiving at least 1 ITN (i.e. reached at distribution)
reportTables.title: Proportion of registered households receiving at least 1 ITN (i.e. reached at distribution)

reportTables.description:
Objective: To monitor registration efforts

Calculation:
- Num: # registered households / population
- Den: # estimated households / population

Action:
If significantly under 100%:
- Check if nearby areas are over 100% (e.g. population movement).
- Consider how birth and death rates might have affected estimates.
- Consider the source and quality of the estimated data (e.g. how long ago was the census, was modelled data used).
- Follow up with areas in case agents need support (possible incomplete reporting or missed households)
reportTables.name: ITN MC - Estimates registered

reportTables.description:
Objective: To monitor issuing across distribution sites

Calculation:
- Num: # ITNs issued
- Den: # ITNs prepositioned

Action:
- If lower than expected, identify and follow-up to ensure reporting. (If all data reported, discern why issuing is slower than expected.)
- If higher than expected, review if other sites are lower than expected and reallocate ITNs accordingly.
reportTables.name: ITN MC - Proportion of prepositioned ITNs issued

reportTables.description:
Objective: To evaluate outcome results and performance of the campaign

Action: Use results to review performance of campaign and identify what went well, what went poorly, and why.
reportTables.name: ITN MC - Outcome indicators (all)

reportTables.description:
Objective: To ensure high quality data

Calculation: Summary form minus Household tracker, per element

Action: If not 0, investigate where the variances occurred and correct data in system accordingly. Continue this until national variance is 0.
reportTables.name: ITN MC - Variances between summary form and household register

reportTables.description:
Objective: To account for all campaign ITNs and highlight variances

Calculation: # ITNs remaining (theoretical) minus # ITNs remaining (reported)

Action: If not 0, investigate where the variances occurred and correct data in system accordingly. Continue this until national variance is 0.
reportTables.name: ITN MC - Remaining stock at end of each day
